{
  "stem": "9168.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I have, in my file in the other room, which I have not pulled for this purpose, a copy of that exhibit that was also offered and admitted into evidence.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Captured German document.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Describing, in graphic detail, graphic-- this experiment [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] signed by Dr.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Sigmund Rascher to his superior, Heinrich Himmler, reporting all of the heil Hitler salutations and everything that went into their-- their terminology and their letterheads, and the addresses.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that-- there were about 380 experimental subjects in this one.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were-- experiments.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm sorry. 380 experiments conducted on about 290 people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were 80 to 90 of those who died from this freezing experiment.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the third experiment charged was malaria, conducted at Dachau, to investigate immunization for the treatment of malaria.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were 1,200 inmate victims who were selected German criminals, taken out of their own prisons, Russian prisoners of war, Yugoslavs, and a large number of Polish Catholic priests who were infected with malaria through controlled infected mosquito bites or by the injection of malaria-infected fresh blood.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Of the 1,200 inmates, there were 14-- I mean, 400 deaths.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the others, of course, suffered the torture, the pain, and permanent disability in many cases.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The fourth experiment charge was mustard gas, which was conducted to investigate the most effective treatment of mustard gas wounds.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And one drop of a liquid gas substance was applied to the lower arm of the experimental subject.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And 10 hours later, burns appeared and-- and spread over the entire body, wherever a liquid drop touched the skin.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Photos were taken by the Nazis daily, which was captured German film used at the trials for conviction.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The fatalities started occurring after the fifth day.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
